message: "If you use ASCEND in academic work, please cite it as follows."
title: "ASCEND: A Comprehensive DevSecOps Framework for Automated Code Scanning, Multi-Track Deployment, and AI-Powered Post-Deployment Synchronization in Enterprise CI/CD"
abstract: >-
  ASCEND is a four-layer DevSecOps framework that integrates automated security
  scanning into CI/CD pipelines with build-gating mechanisms, multi-track
  deployment orchestration, and AI-powered post-deployment code synchronization.
  The framework provides reference configurations across GitHub Actions, GitLab
  CI/CD, Jenkins, and Azure DevOps with detailed integration patterns for SAST,
  DAST, SCA, and IaC scanning. A novel AI synchronization layer employs
  AST-based drift detection, ML conflict classification, and LLM-based conflict
  resolution with formal verification. Empirical evaluation across 12 enterprise
  repositories over six months demonstrates an 83.0% reduction in
  pre-production critical vulnerabilities, a 43.5% decrease in mean time to
  deployment, a 171.9% increase in deployment frequency, and 94.2% accuracy in
  AI-assisted conflict resolution; all primary comparisons are statistically
  significant (p < 0.001) with large effect sizes (Cohen's d > 2.0).
